Some of my parts can take a long time to print, sometimes even hours. Not wanting to be 'chained' to the printer, I found an Elcom 3 megapixel webcam capable of 720p HD video capture.
The Elcom camera unit rotates in its mount, so I just stripped off the stock mount and designed a replacement that snaps over the top front edge of my Tantillus printer case.

This was printed in PLA with 150 micron layers and 15% infill.
Note: My Tantillus is one of the original prototype units and the acrylic case is slightly thinner than the production units. You may need to adjust some of the dimensions to fit your particular printer.

BGRL-HA02A Apparently Thingiverse likes toilet roll holders. This is yet another speculative - and if I may say so myself, slightly weird - design for a batchelor-friendly toilet roll holder using the same spline fitting as the previous BGRL-H01A and it's more functionally evolved form, the BGRL-H03A. By batchelor-friendly, I mean that if there was a carrier tube to remove or otherwise require the user to do something other than just remove the roll then the roll would never be changed. So this design allows the user to just slip the spent roll off the carrier tube with no additional effort. This was adapted from the aforementioned BGRL-H01A by slicing off one of the arms and re-manipulating the left arm to support the load of a roll by itself. That has lead to slight size tolerance issues for the roll. I might alter the dimensions later but it appears to work right now. Use with BGRLM-M01A (wall mount). Optional accessory:
TPRS-M01A prevents toilet roll sliding around carrier tube. Version History:
V1 - original Build time / particulars:
~ 3 hours in Standard mode on Makerbot 2. No supports needed.

This is a remix of the fantastic design by JuliaDee. It is exactly the same enclosure design, but I have remixed the grommets to suit the magnets available to me in the UK. Lexan panels 2.0 mm x 320w x 355h, fastened to the mighty Zortrax by neodymium magnets held in printed ABS grommet/handles. I used 6.35 mm (1/4") x 9.53 mm (3/8") N42 magnets from First4Magnets in the UK - they sell them as a pack of 10 - 3 for the left and right sides and 4 for the front ! http://www.first4magnets.com/cylindrical-rod-magnets-c39/6-35mm-1-4-dia-x-9-53mm-3-8-thick-n42-neodymium-magnet-1-68kg-pull-p3838 The grommets fit into holes drilled into the Lexan with a 10mm step bit and can be solvent-welded with MEK or glued with epoxy.

author: gregory-gk

description.text: Replacement parts for the 1986 boardgame "Fireball Island" (http://boardgamegeek.com/boardgame/1768/fireball-island). A lot of the piece from my copy of this game were either broken or lost, so I created replacement charm tokens, and a replacement marble-breathing skull for the center of the board. The center piece is based on a skull I found on thingiverse. I always felt it should have been a skull.

All pieces printed without supports.  
The "mouth-hole" is too small for regular sized marbles, so you may need to increase the size depending.

comments.text: Nice skull model! I've created a website to gather all board game improvements to inspire and showcase. Would you be interested in adding them to the Board Game Level Up site? I could help you with it, but still giving you the credit. www.boardgamelevelup.com
comments.author: RobhJ
